							<h2 class="text-4xl text-strongpink">Nostr for Tomorrow</h2>
							<div class="text-xl mt-2">Nostr, an acronym for  “Notes and Other Stuff Transmitted by Relays”, revolutionizes social networking and online communication by eliminating dependency on centralized servers. It employs a client-relay model, where users run clients, and anyone can operate relays. Information (and its storage) are distributed throughout a network of individuals, passionate volunteers, businesses, and nonprofits alike.</div>
							<div class="mt-2 text-neutral-500 dark:text-neutral-300">The Nostr protocol ensures tamperproof communication through cryptographic keys and signatures. By enabling users to establish pathways for publishing notes to relays and incentivizing the deployment and maintenence of unique, independent relays by operators, Nostr addresses many shortcomings of the current web. From interoperable applications to unique and ubiquitous identities, Nostr opens doors to creative, collabrotive innovation like the wrold has never seen before.</div>
